narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I gained more insight in how to create good research presentations that are clear, concise, and effective at bringing the message across that is appropriate for the given audience. I also gained more practice in reading and critically evaluating scientific literature.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I really like the level of faculty involvement in the course and how they work with students on their presentations. I wish we didn't have to send in questions so far in advance because I'd rather read the papers closer to when the presentation is, but I can see that the students need more time to process the questions we send.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I think this is a great course for those entering their PhDs as it allows one to have practice in critically analyzing literature and working together with colleagues to present the findings.
